The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Munro in San Diego, California to commend the crew for capturing 39,000 pounds of cocaine at sea. He highlighted the importance of the Coast Guard's work in preventing drugs from reaching American communities and emphasized the need to secure the southern border to stop drug trafficking. Pence also mentioned his upcoming visit to a detention facility at the southern border and criticized Democrats who referred to U.S. Customs and Border facilities as "concentration camps." He addressed concerns about the conditions in detention centers and stated that the system is overwhelmed. Pence also discussed the need to reform asylum laws and mentioned the ongoing criminal matter involving Congressman Duncan Hunter.